.SH NAME
md__b_u_i_l_d___i_n_s_t_r_u_c_t_i_o_n_s \- RogueCity Solution Build - Quick Start Guide 
.PP

.SH "What Changed"
.PP
Your project has been refactored to use a \fBVisual Studio solution\fP (\fRbuild_vs/RogueCities\&.sln\fP) generated by CMake\&. This provides better integration with Visual Studio and organized project structure\&.
.SS "Solution Structure"
The solution contains these key projects:

.PP
.IP "1." 4
\fBRogueCityCore\fP - Core library (data types, math)
.IP "2." 4
\fBRogueCityGenerators\fP - Procedural generation algorithms
.IP "3." 4
\fBRogueCityApp\fP - Application layer (HFSM, integration)
.IP "4." 4
\fBRogueCityAI\fP - AI assistant integration
.IP "5." 4
\fBRogueCityImGui\fP - ImGui library wrapper
.IP "6." 4
\fBRogueCityVisualizerGui\fP ? - Main GUI application (your startup project)
.IP "7." 4
\fBRogueCityVisualizerHeadless\fP - Headless version
.IP "8." 4
Test projects (test_core, test_generators, test_editor_hfsm, etc\&.)
.PP
.SS "Output Location"
Built executables are now in: \fRbin/RogueCityVisualizerGui\&.exe\fP
.SH "How to Build and Run"
.PP
.SS "Option 1: Visual Studio (Recommended)"
.PP
.nf
# Open the solution in Visual Studio
start build_vs\\RogueCities\&.sln
.fi
.PP

.PP
Then:
.IP "1." 4
Set \fBRogueCityVisualizerGui\fP as startup project (right-click ? Set as Startup Project)
.IP "2." 4
Select \fBRelease\fP or \fBDebug\fP configuration
.IP "3." 4
Press \fBF5\fP to build and run
.PP
.SS "Option 2: Command Line"
.PP
.nf
# Build
cmake \-\-build build_vs \-\-target RogueCityVisualizerGui \-\-config Release \-\-parallel 4

# Run
\&.\\bin\\RogueCityVisualizerGui\&.exe
.fi
.PP
.SS "Option 3: Quick Script"
Simply run the provided batch script:

.PP
.PP
.nf
\&.\\build_and_run\&.bat
.fi
.PP
.SH "Configuration"
.PP
If you need to reconfigure the build (e\&.g\&., after pulling new changes), run:

.PP
.PP
.nf
cmake \-B build_vs \-S \&. \-DROGUECITY_BUILD_VISUALIZER=ON
.fi
.PP
.SH "Geometry Migration Flags"
.PP
The build now supports dual geometry backend flags for incremental migration:

.PP
.PP
.nf
# Legacy path (GEOS if available, otherwise legacy shim)
cmake \-B build_vs \-S \&. \-DUSE_LEGACY_GEOS=ON

# Boost\&.Geometry path (falls back to legacy shim if Boost is unavailable)
cmake \-B build_vs \-S \&. \-DUSE_LEGACY_GEOS=OFF
.fi
.PP

.PP
Recommended vcpkg install command for migration dependencies:

.PP
.PP
.nf
vcpkg install boost\-geometry fastnoise2 nanoflann delaunator\-cpp
.fi
.PP

.PP
Optional terrain backend is auto-detected from \fR3rdparty/SLTerrainGeneration\fP when:

.PP
.PP
.nf
\-DROGUECITY_ENABLE_SLTERRAIN=ON
.fi
.PP
